1: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, one of your [[action]] scores (GM's choice) increases by 1.
2: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, one of your [[attribute]] scores (GM's choice) increases by 1.
3: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you rapidly regenerate from physical harm.
4: When you physically attack while [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, gain +1 [[impact]].
5: When you attempt to move quickly while [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, gain +1 [[impact]].
6: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can cast one [[cantrip|spell tier]] [[spell]] (chosen by the GM).
7: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can cast one [[uncommon-tier|spell tier]] [[spell]] (chosen by the GM) from it up to four times per day.
8: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can cast one [[rare-tier|spell tier]] [[spell]] (chosen by the GM) from it up to twice per day.
9: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can cast one [[epic-tier|spell tier]] [[spell]] (chosen by the GM) from it once per day.
10: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can't be blinded, deafened, or petrified.
11: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you are immune to disease and resistant to all poisons.
12: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you can't be charmed or frightened.
13: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you have resistance against one [[damage type]] of the GM's choice.
14: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you gain one [[talent]] of the GM's choice.
15: While [[attuned|attunement]] to the artifact, you gain [[advantage]] when actively defending against physical damage.